	(text_box "Three dedicated test point rails are provided to simplify hardware bring-up and real-time debugging. The layout of these rails on the schematic mirrors their physical placement on the PCB edges for intuitive probing.\n\nHardware Specifications:\n\nFootprint: Designed for Keystone 5015 (or low-cost RH-5051 clones).\n\nCompatibility: Optimized for hook-style and alligator clip probes commonly used with oscilloscopes and logic analyzers.\n\nSignal Domains:\n\nANALOG RAIL (Top): Monitoring for motor sensing (VSNA/B) and user feedback (Potentiometer/NTC).\n\nDIGITAL RAIL (Bottom): Debugging for MCU status, UART comms, and the DXL direction control (TX_EN).\n\nDRIVER RAIL (Left): Direct access to power inputs (VBAT, VUSB, VEXT), the primary VSYS rail, and motor outputs (MOT_A/B)."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 209.55 29.21 0)
		(size 72.39 101.6)
